From: bentoo overlay
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] modulefinder: silence type-arg error for generic PathSpec

pathspec >= 1.0.0 makes PathSpec a Generic[TPattern_co], so mypy's
self-check (run via mypyc during build) raises [type-arg] on the
unparameterized return annotation. Upstream master fixed this by
switching to GitIgnoreSpec (a non-generic subclass), but that is a
larger refactor; for 1.20.2 we just suppress the diagnostic on the
single offending line.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/ (bentoo overlay)
--- a/mypy/modulefinder.py
+++ b/mypy/modulefinder.py
@@ -724,7 +724,7 @@ def matches_exclude(


 @functools.lru_cache
-def find_gitignores(dir: str) -> list[tuple[str, PathSpec]]:
+def find_gitignores(dir: str) -> list[tuple[str, PathSpec]]:  # type: ignore[type-arg]
     parent_dir = os.path.dirname(dir)
     if parent_dir == dir or os.path.exists(os.path.join(dir, ".git")):
         parent_gitignores = []
